===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|reyn|lang=enm}}, {{term|rein|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|regn|reġn|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|regnaz|lang=gem-pro}} (compare West Frisian {{term|rein|lang=fy}}, Dutch {{term|regen|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Regen|lang=de}}, Danish {{term|regn|lang=da}}), from pre-Germanic {{recons|Hréǵ-no}}-, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|Hreǵ|lang=ine-pro}} 'to flow' (compare Latin {{term|rigo|rigō|wet, soak|lang=la}}, Lithuanian {{term|rõki|lang=lt}} 'drizzling rain', Albanian {{term|rrjedh|lang=sq}} 'to flow, drip').

